-- National Bank of Oman to Offer Islamic Services, Observer Says
-- B y   R o b e r t   T u t t l e
-- 2011-12-21T14:21:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/national-bank-of-oman-to-offer-islamic-services-observer-says.html
National Bank of Oman SAOG (NBOB)  plans to
offer Islamic banking services after gaining approval from the
country’s central bank, the  Oman Daily Observer said , citing the
bank’s Deputy Chairman Mohammed al-Ardhi.  The bank seeks diversification in offering Shariah-
compliant lending, al-Ardhi said, according to the Observer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Tuttle in Doha at 
 rtuttle@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  